WEBVTT

1
00:03:34.548 --> 00:03:35.757
There.

2
00:03:36.174 --> 00:03:37.968
Technicals, nine o'clock.

3
00:04:03.452 --> 00:04:05.162
Oh, shit! Did you see that?

4
00:04:05.328 --> 00:04:09.458
Chief, we got unarmed civilians
getting shot down here at nine o'clock.

5
00:04:09.666 --> 00:04:12.836
I got it, Matt.
I don't think we can touch this.

6
00:04:20.886 --> 00:04:22.262
Command, Super 64...

7
00:04:22.345 --> 00:04:26.057
...we got militia shooting civilians
at the food distribution center.

8
00:04:26.433 --> 00:04:28.393
Request permission to engage.

9
00:04:28.477 --> 00:04:30.812
Super 64, are you taking fire? Over.

10
00:04:31.354 --> 00:04:32.814
Negative, command.

11
00:04:32.939 --> 00:04:36.568
U.N.'s jurisdiction, 64.
We cannot intervene.

12
00:04:36.693 --> 00:04:38.361
-Return to base. Over.
-Roger.

13
00:04:38.945 --> 00:04:40.697
64 returning.

14
00:05:41.675 --> 00:05:42.551
Leaving.

15
00:06:47.657 --> 00:06:49.409
General Garrison?

16
00:06:49.492 --> 00:06:50.827
No, thanks. I got one.

17
00:06:51.036 --> 00:06:52.829
But these are Cuban.

18
00:06:53.163 --> 00:06:55.040
Bolivar Belicoso.

19
00:06:55.498 --> 00:06:56.499
So is this.

20
00:06:58.919 --> 00:07:01.004
Miami, my friend, is not Cuba.

21
00:07:08.553 --> 00:07:11.514
I see not catching Aidid
IS becoming a routine.

22
00:07:12.474 --> 00:07:15.393
We weren't trying to catch Aidid.
We were trying to catch you.

23
00:07:15.477 --> 00:07:16.311
Me?

24
00:07:16.853 --> 00:07:18.772
But am I that important?

25
00:07:19.147 --> 00:07:20.732
I hardly think so.

26
00:07:20.899 --> 00:07:23.944
-You're just a businessman.
-Trying to make a living.

27
00:07:24.152 --> 00:07:26.863
Yeah. Selling guns to Aidid's militia.

28
00:07:31.910 --> 00:07:33.411
You've been here, what?

29
00:07:34.996 --> 00:07:36.539
Six weeks?

30
00:07:38.667 --> 00:07:41.795
Six weeks
you are trying to catch the general.

31
00:07:42.295 --> 00:07:44.506
You put up reward posters.

32
00:07:45.006 --> 00:07:49.260
$25,000. What is this?
Gunfight at the K.O. Corral?

33
00:07:50.512 --> 00:07:53.515
It's the O.K. Corral.

34
00:07:54.015 --> 00:07:58.186
Do you think bringing me in
will make him suddenly come to you?

35
00:07:58.395 --> 00:08:00.563
Make him more agreeable?

36
00:08:03.108 --> 00:08:05.151
You know where he sleeps.

37
00:08:05.735 --> 00:08:09.239
You pay for his beds, much less his militia.

38
00:08:11.032 --> 00:08:14.119
We're not leaving Somalia till we find him.

39
00:08:15.745 --> 00:08:16.955
And we will find him.

40
00:08:17.038 --> 00:08:19.666
Don't think because I grew up
without running water...

41
00:08:19.749 --> 00:08:21.751
... am simple, General.

42
00:08:22.752 --> 00:08:25.130
I do know something about history.

43
00:08:25.714 --> 00:08:30.135
See all this? It's simply shaping tomorrow.

44
00:08:30.760 --> 00:08:34.764
A tomorrow without a lot
of Arkansas white boys' ideas in it.

45
00:08:35.473 --> 00:08:38.351
Well, I wouldn't know about that.
I'm from Texas.

46
00:08:38.560 --> 00:08:42.689
Mr. Garrison,
I think you shouldn't have come here.

47
00:08:43.273 --> 00:08:45.191
This is civil war.

48
00:08:46.151 --> 00:08:47.986
This is our war.

49
00:08:48.737 --> 00:08:49.988
Not yours.

50
00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:54.492
300,000 dead and counting.

51
00:08:54.743 --> 00:08:58.079
That's not a war, Mr. Atto.
That's genocide.

52
00:08:59.581 --> 00:09:02.167
Now, you enjoy that tea, you hear?

53
00:09:07.839 --> 00:09:09.632
How'd he strike you?

54
00:09:09.758 --> 00:09:12.886
Urbane, sophisticated, cruel.

55
00:09:12.969 --> 00:09:14.721
Yeah, he's a good catch.

56
00:09:15.180 --> 00:09:17.557
It'll take time, but Aidid will feel the loss.

57
00:09:17.640 --> 00:09:20.477
I'm not sure time is something we got
in great supply.

58
00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:24.731
This isn't Iraq, you know.
Much more complicated than that.

59
00:09:25.148 --> 00:09:27.150
Boss, most of Washington might disagree.

60
00:09:27.233 --> 00:09:31.404
They've been calling for situation reports
every morning this week.

61
00:09:32.489 --> 00:09:36.826
Well, tell them the situation is fragile.

62
00:09:43.541 --> 00:09:46.002
Ladies and gentlemen,
I'm Cliff "Elvis" Wolcott.

63
00:09:46.169 --> 00:09:47.837
I'll be your pilot today.

64
00:09:47.879 --> 00:09:52.008
Federal regulations designate this
a non-smoking Black Hawk helicopter.

65
00:09:52.050 --> 00:09:56.387
Those in Mogadishu frequent flyer program
will earn 100 free credits.

66
00:09:56.596 --> 00:10:01.142
And as always, the air sickness bags
are in the seat back in front of you.

67
00:10:02.185 --> 00:10:05.021
Number one indications are good, Cliff.
Put her on two.

68
00:10:05.313 --> 00:10:06.523
You're still clear.

69
00:10:21.746 --> 00:10:25.041
61, this is 64. Go to UHF secure.

70
00:10:25.250 --> 00:10:26.417
I've got some bad news.

71
00:10:27.585 --> 00:10:30.338
"Limo" is a word, Durant.
I don't want to hear about it.

72
00:10:30.588 --> 00:10:33.258
It is not a word.
It's an abbreviation of a word.

73
00:10:33.466 --> 00:10:35.426
"Limo" is a word in common usage.

74
00:10:35.593 --> 00:10:39.305
That is the key phrase in Scrabble,
my good friend. Common usage.

75
00:10:39.472 --> 00:10:42.475
If it's not in the dictionary it doesn't count!

76
00:10:42.559 --> 00:10:44.644
It doesn't have to be in the dictionary!

77
00:10:44.727 --> 00:10:46.896
It does have to be in the dictionary!

78
00:10:46.980 --> 00:10:50.275
When we get back to the base,
it's coming off.

79
00:10:51.192 --> 00:10:53.987
You touch my "limo”
and I'll spank you, Night stalker.

80
00:10:54.612 --> 00:10:56.197
Yeah, promises.

81
00:10:56.906 --> 00:10:58.700
That's a nice beach down there.

82
00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:00.451
How's the water?

83
00:11:00.952 --> 00:11:04.831
Yeah, it's nice and warm.
And it's loaded with sharks.

84
00:11:11.004 --> 00:11:12.505
-Name.
-Todd.

85
00:11:12.881 --> 00:11:14.632
-Last name.
-Blackburn.

86
00:11:16.426 --> 00:11:18.136
First name, Todd.

87
00:11:18.428 --> 00:11:21.264
-So, what's it like?
-What's what like?

88
00:11:21.472 --> 00:11:22.724
Mogadishu. The fighting.

89
00:11:22.849 --> 00:11:26.728
-Serial number.
-72163427.

90
00:11:27.937 --> 00:11:31.608
Firstly, it's "the Mog" or simply "Mog."
No one calls it Mogadishu here.

91
00:11:31.649 --> 00:11:35.069
Secondly, I wouldn't know
about the fighting, so don't ask.

92
00:11:35.653 --> 00:11:36.654
Why not?

93
00:11:37.155 --> 00:11:38.781
Didn't I just say, "Don't ask"?

94
00:11:41.242 --> 00:11:44.954
You look like you're about 12,
so let me explain something to you.

95
00:11:45.038 --> 00:11:48.625
I have a rare and mysterious skill
that precludes me from doing missions.

96
00:11:50.084 --> 00:11:51.044
Typing.

97
00:11:51.127 --> 00:11:53.546
-Can you type?
-No.

98
00:11:54.881 --> 00:11:58.009
-Date of birth.
-2-27-75.

99
00:12:03.973 --> 00:12:05.850
Well, I'm here to kick some ass.

100
00:12:10.688 --> 00:12:12.148
Let's bring it in.

101
00:12:27.830 --> 00:12:29.582
Nice, man! Very smooth!

102
00:12:29.999 --> 00:12:31.834
Single shot through the engine block.

103
00:12:32.502 --> 00:12:35.213
Shit, that's a shame. That was a nice jeep.

104
00:12:58.987 --> 00:13:01.281
Cease fire! Cease fire!

105
00:13:01.948 --> 00:13:02.991
Check your weapons!

106
00:13:03.199 --> 00:13:04.200
Sergeant Eversmann.

107
00:13:08.579 --> 00:13:10.039
Private First Class Blackburn.

108
00:13:10.373 --> 00:13:11.374
Yeah?

109
00:13:12.000 --> 00:13:13.042
Reporting for duty.

110
00:13:13.710 --> 00:13:18.047
Not to me. You're reporting to Lt. Beales.
He should be here somewhere.

111
00:13:18.214 --> 00:13:19.382
Can I leave him with you?

112
00:13:20.383 --> 00:13:22.385
Yeah, go ahead.

113
00:13:22.760 --> 00:13:24.679
-You brought your weapon.
-Yes, sir.

114
00:13:25.013 --> 00:13:26.806
Want me to shoot? I'm rested.

115
00:13:27.140 --> 00:13:30.059
-When did you get in?
-Just now, Sergeant.

116
00:13:34.939 --> 00:13:36.065
Hey, who's hungry?

117
00:13:58.588 --> 00:14:01.924
What is this, Sarg'nt?
Another taxpayer-funded Delta safari?

118
00:14:02.216 --> 00:14:05.219
-Not if General Garrison is asking.
-I'm asking.

119
00:14:06.095 --> 00:14:07.597
Have a nice meal, Captain.

120
00:14:12.435 --> 00:14:14.729
-Hey, man, there's a line.
- know.

121
00:14:15.146 --> 00:14:18.566
-Well, this isn't the back of it.
-Yeah, I know.

122
00:14:19.901 --> 00:14:22.111
Sergeant. Sergeant.

123
00:14:22.779 --> 00:14:23.988
What's going on here?

124
00:14:24.072 --> 00:14:27.116
Some aerial target practice, sir.
Didn't want to leave it behind.

125
00:14:27.158 --> 00:14:29.327
I'm talking about your weapon.

126
00:14:29.452 --> 00:14:32.038
Delta or no Delta, that's a hot weapon.

127
00:14:32.205 --> 00:14:35.500
You know better than that.
Safety should be on at all times on base.

128
00:14:35.583 --> 00:14:37.960
Well, this is my safety, sir.

129
00:14:40.755 --> 00:14:43.716
Let it go, sir.
The guy hasn't eaten in a couple of days.

130
00:14:43.800 --> 00:14:46.636
You Delta boys
are a bunch of undisciplined cowboys.

131
00:14:47.470 --> 00:14:49.305
Let me tell you something, Sarg'nt.

132
00:14:49.514 --> 00:14:53.309
When we get on a five-yard line,
you're going to need my Rangers.

133
00:14:53.351 --> 00:14:55.436
Y'all better learn to be team players.

134
00:14:57.188 --> 00:14:58.689
We're done here.

135
00:15:08.324 --> 00:15:11.828
Speak up. You say this is your safety?

136
00:15:11.994 --> 00:15:13.830
Well, this is my boot, son.

137
00:15:14.664 --> 00:15:18.084
And it will fit up your ass
with the proper amount of force.

138
00:15:18.292 --> 00:15:21.921
-Is that a Jersey accent?
-I'm trying to do this, give me a break.

139
00:15:22.130 --> 00:15:24.006
Take those sunglasses off.

140
00:15:24.132 --> 00:15:26.467
Delta wants to wear Oakleys,
that's their business.

141
00:15:26.509 --> 00:15:28.761
I don't want to see them on you again.

142
00:15:30.513 --> 00:15:32.223
Is that a hot weapon?

143
00:15:37.562 --> 00:15:38.938
Is that your move?

144
00:15:39.105 --> 00:15:40.982
Is my hand on the piece?

145
00:15:41.357 --> 00:15:43.776
I can mate you in three whatever you do.

146
00:15:45.236 --> 00:15:48.531
I'd keep my eye on that queen
before counseling others.

147
00:15:49.198 --> 00:15:51.159
Well, she's just lying in wait.

148
00:15:55.037 --> 00:15:56.038
Yikes.

149
00:15:58.291 --> 00:16:01.294
It's good. You're really improving.

150
00:16:01.794 --> 00:16:04.380
If I may make a suggestion-- Observation.

151
00:16:04.589 --> 00:16:05.590
Go ahead.

152
00:16:05.840 --> 00:16:08.176
-It's a children's book, right?
-Right.

153
00:16:08.759 --> 00:16:12.889
They are not supposed to scare
the living shit out of the children.

154
00:16:13.055 --> 00:16:16.809
This is the part of the story
where our knight is slaying the dragon.

155
00:16:16.893 --> 00:16:19.562
That's scary.
Besides, my daughter loves this stuff.

156
00:16:19.604 --> 00:16:21.606
Thought you finished that last week.

157
00:16:22.231 --> 00:16:23.524
You done?

158
00:16:25.067 --> 00:16:28.571
Hey, we are at the 10-yard line here, men.

159
00:16:28.738 --> 00:16:30.239
You understand?

160
00:16:30.740 --> 00:16:33.242
Can you count? One, two, ten.

161
00:16:33.743 --> 00:16:35.912
Okay? Where are my running backs?

162
00:16:36.120 --> 00:16:37.914
Where are my running backs?

163
00:16:39.415 --> 00:16:42.585
Hey, I didn't see you at church on Sunday.

164
00:16:42.752 --> 00:16:44.712
You had something more important to do?

165
00:16:44.921 --> 00:16:47.340
Not on Sunday, you don't. Not anymore.

166
00:16:47.423 --> 00:16:49.717
I will make you believe, you understand?

167
00:17:04.941 --> 00:17:06.359
Pretty funny, hoo-ah?

168
00:17:09.403 --> 00:17:12.949
It was a good impression.
I recognize myself.

169
00:17:15.409 --> 00:17:17.203
All right, carry on.

170
00:17:17.912 --> 00:17:20.748
-I'd like a word, specialist.
-Sir.

171
00:17:21.415 --> 00:17:24.919
You understand why we have
a chain of command, don't you?

172
00:17:25.086 --> 00:17:25.962
Roger that, sir.

173
00:17:26.045 --> 00:17:29.549
If you ever undermine me again,
you'll clean latrines with your tongue...

174
00:17:29.632 --> 00:17:32.635
...till you taste no difference
between shit and French fries.

175
00:17:32.718 --> 00:17:33.844
-Are we clear?
-Hoo-ah, sir.

176
00:17:33.928 --> 00:17:34.845
All right.

177
00:17:42.728 --> 00:17:43.771
Listen to this:

178
00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:48.609
If one skinny kills another his clan owes
the dead guy's clan a hundred camels.

179
00:17:48.943 --> 00:17:50.152
A hundred camels.

180
00:17:50.361 --> 00:17:52.613
Camels. I wouldn't pay one camel.

181
00:17:53.114 --> 00:17:55.032
Must be a lot of fucking camel debt.

182
00:17:55.866 --> 00:17:57.743
Is that really true, Lieutenant?

183
00:17:57.952 --> 00:17:59.996
Ask Sgt. Eversmann. He likes skinnies.

184
00:18:00.413 --> 00:18:03.040
Sgt. Eversmann,
you really like the skinnies?

185
00:18:03.499 --> 00:18:07.211
It's not that I like them or I don't like them.
I respect them.

186
00:18:07.378 --> 00:18:11.549
See, what you guys fail to realize
Is the sergeant is a bit of an idealist.

187
00:18:12.174 --> 00:18:15.595
He believes in this mission
down to his bones. Don't you, Sergeant?

188
00:18:15.845 --> 00:18:19.098
Look, these people, they have no jobs...

189
00:18:19.348 --> 00:18:23.436
...no food, no education, no future.

190
00:18:23.519 --> 00:18:27.106
I just figure that, I mean,
we have two things that we can do.

191
00:18:27.189 --> 00:18:28.691
We can help...

192
00:18:28.774 --> 00:18:32.194
...or we can sit back and watch
the country destroy itself on CNN.

193
00:18:32.278 --> 00:18:33.279
Right?

194
00:18:33.613 --> 00:18:36.574
I don't know about you guys,
but I was trained to fight.

195
00:18:36.782 --> 00:18:38.868
Are you trained to fight, Sergeant?

196
00:18:38.909 --> 00:18:41.704
Well, I think I was trained
to make a difference, Kurth.

197
00:18:42.872 --> 00:18:45.249
Like the man said, he's an idealist.

198
00:18:47.043 --> 00:18:49.086
Oh, wait. This is my favorite part.

199
00:18:54.634 --> 00:18:56.510
Stay away from the cans!

200
00:18:56.719 --> 00:18:59.096
Die, gas-pumper!

201
00:18:59.764 --> 00:19:01.557
Stay away from those cans!

202
00:19:06.479 --> 00:19:08.606
No, no, stay back.

203
00:19:08.689 --> 00:19:11.692
He's having a seizure.
Put something in his mouth.

204
00:19:11.734 --> 00:19:16.697
John, it's okay. John, it's okay. It's okay.

205
00:20:03.077 --> 00:20:05.913
Well, he'll be fine. But not in this army.

206
00:20:06.914 --> 00:20:09.583
He's out of the game.
He's epileptic, going home.

207
00:20:14.088 --> 00:20:16.716
I'm putting you in charge of his chalk.

208
00:20:17.133 --> 00:20:19.969
-You got a problem with that?
-No, sir.

209
00:20:20.052 --> 00:20:22.138
It's a big responsibility.

210
00:20:22.221 --> 00:20:24.807
Your men will look to you
to make the right decisions.

211
00:20:24.849 --> 00:20:26.934
They're lives depend on it.

212
00:20:27.977 --> 00:20:29.228
All right.

213
00:20:29.895 --> 00:20:32.857
-Rangers lead the way, sir.
-All the way.

214
00:20:33.065 --> 00:20:34.483
Good luck.

215
00:21:18.027 --> 00:21:22.823
<i>A meeting of Aidid's senior cabinet
may take place today at 1500 hours.</i>

216
00:21:23.657 --> 00:21:26.368
I say "may" because we all know by now...

217
00:21:26.577 --> 00:21:29.872
...with the intel we get on the street,
nothing is certain.

218
00:21:30.039 --> 00:21:32.875
This is actual intel
confirmed by three sources.

219
00:21:33.709 --> 00:21:36.796
Two tier-one personalities may be present:

220
00:21:37.254 --> 00:21:41.300
Omar Salad, Aidid's top political advisor...

221
00:21:41.383 --> 00:21:43.969
...and Abdi Hassan Awale, interior minister.

222
00:21:44.053 --> 00:21:46.055
These are the guys we're after.

223
00:21:46.889 --> 00:21:48.265
Today we go.

224
00:21:48.849 --> 00:21:51.352
Same mission template as before.

225
00:21:51.560 --> 00:21:55.689
1545, Assault Force Delta
will infiltrate the target building...

226
00:21:55.898 --> 00:21:58.067
...and seize all suspects within.

227
00:21:58.275 --> 00:22:02.196
Security Force Rangers: 4 Ranger chalks,
under command of Capt. Steele...

228
00:22:02.238 --> 00:22:04.532
...will rope in at 1546...

229
00:22:04.657 --> 00:22:08.035
...and hold a four-corner perimeter
around the target building.

230
00:22:08.577 --> 00:22:09.912
No one gets in or out.

231
00:22:10.162 --> 00:22:11.705
Extraction Force:

232
00:22:11.997 --> 00:22:16.544
Lt. Colonel McKnight's humvee column
will drive in at 1547...

233
00:22:16.752 --> 00:22:20.673
...on Hawlwadig Road
and hold just short of the Olympic Hotel.

234
00:22:20.881 --> 00:22:22.341
Wait for the green light.

235
00:22:22.550 --> 00:22:24.426
Now once Delta gives the word...

236
00:22:24.635 --> 00:22:29.348
...McKnight's column will go to the target
and load the prisoners onto trucks.

237
00:22:29.932 --> 00:22:32.309
Immediately after
the prisoners are loaded...

238
00:22:32.476 --> 00:22:36.605
...the four Ranger chalks
will collapse back to the target building...

239
00:22:36.814 --> 00:22:38.190
...load up on humvees...

240
00:22:38.399 --> 00:22:42.278
...and the entire ground force
will exfil the 3 miles back to base.

241
00:22:42.570 --> 00:22:45.781
Mission time, no longer than 30 minutes.

242
00:22:46.907 --> 00:22:51.745
Now, I had requested light armor
and AC-130 Spectre gunships...

243
00:22:51.954 --> 00:22:56.000
...but Washington, in all its wisdom,
decided against this.

244
00:22:56.208 --> 00:22:58.043
Too high-profile.

245
00:22:58.294 --> 00:23:01.463
So Black Hawks and Little Birds
will provide the air cover...

246
00:23:01.672 --> 00:23:03.883
...with miniguns and 2.75 rockets.

247
00:23:04.133 --> 00:23:05.467
Colonel Harrell.

248
00:23:05.676 --> 00:23:10.014
In the C-2 bird, Colonel Matthews
will coordinate the air mission...

249
00:23:10.514 --> 00:23:13.350
...and I will coordinate ground forces.

250
00:23:13.684 --> 00:23:14.977
Colonel Matthews.

251
00:23:15.060 --> 00:23:18.355
Mission launch code word is Irene.

252
00:23:18.814 --> 00:23:19.815
Questions?

253
00:23:23.068 --> 00:23:24.403
Which building is it, sir?

254
00:23:24.945 --> 00:23:28.532
We're confirming that now.
Somewhere near the Bakara market.

255
00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:34.163
I don't choose the time or place
of their meetings.

256
00:23:34.330 --> 00:23:36.165
I didn't say a word, sir.

257
00:23:36.457 --> 00:23:39.835
Make no mistake,
once you're in the Bakara market...

258
00:23:39.919 --> 00:23:42.338
...you're in an entirely hostile district.

259
00:23:42.838 --> 00:23:45.215
Don't underestimate their capabilities.

260
00:23:45.466 --> 00:23:49.053
We'll be in friendly neighborhoods
before we hit the market...

261
00:23:49.178 --> 00:23:53.891
...80 remember the rules of engagement:
No one fires unless fired upon.

262
00:23:54.058 --> 00:23:56.352
Now, let's go get this thing done.

263
00:23:57.436 --> 00:23:59.063
Good luck, gentlemen.

264
00:24:04.026 --> 00:24:06.946
What's the matter, Danny?
Something you don't like?

265
00:24:07.154 --> 00:24:09.365
No Spectre gunships,
daylight instead of night...

266
00:24:09.531 --> 00:24:12.034
...afternoon when they're all fucked up
on khat...

267
00:24:12.201 --> 00:24:16.372
...only part of the city Aidid can mount
a counter-attack on short notice....

268
00:24:16.705 --> 00:24:19.625
-What's not to like?
-Life's imperfect.

269
00:24:19.833 --> 00:24:23.545
For you two, circling above it at 500 feet,
it's imperfect.

270
00:24:23.796 --> 00:24:27.466
Down in the street, it's unforgiving.

271
00:25:03.627 --> 00:25:04.920
What the fuck, Smith?

272
00:25:05.921 --> 00:25:07.798
-Well?
-Well, what?

273
00:25:07.965 --> 00:25:09.425
We going?

274
00:25:10.801 --> 00:25:14.596
-Why should I tell you that?
-Because I'm me.

275
00:25:15.931 --> 00:25:19.601
Yeah. 3:00. Downtown.

276
00:25:19.810 --> 00:25:21.353
-Bakara market.
-All right.

277
00:25:21.603 --> 00:25:25.441
Listen, Smith, I need you to back me up
out there today, all right?

278
00:25:25.607 --> 00:25:26.817
Keep sharp.

279
00:25:29.486 --> 00:25:31.613
Yes, sir, Sergeant Eversmann.

280
00:25:31.822 --> 00:25:34.199
Ev, it's going to be nothing, man.

281
00:25:34.825 --> 00:25:36.118
Nothing.

282
00:25:38.996 --> 00:25:44.334
It's all in the grind, Sizemore.
Can't be too fine, can't be too coarse.

283
00:25:44.960 --> 00:25:47.129
This, my friend, is a science.

284
00:25:48.005 --> 00:25:50.841
You're looking at the guy
that believed the commercials.

285
00:25:51.050 --> 00:25:53.177
About "be all you can be."

286
00:25:53.385 --> 00:25:56.180
I made coffee through Desert Storm.

287
00:25:56.472 --> 00:25:59.683
I made coffee through Panama,
while everyone else got to fight...

288
00:25:59.892 --> 00:26:01.727
...got to be a Ranger.

289
00:26:02.436 --> 00:26:07.274
Now it's "Grimesy, black, one sugar"
or "Grimesy, got a powdered anywhere?"

290
00:26:11.153 --> 00:26:13.655
-What happened to you?
-Ping-Pong accident.

291
00:26:13.989 --> 00:26:14.990
What?

292
00:26:15.991 --> 00:26:17.326
So guess what.

293
00:26:17.951 --> 00:26:20.746
Your wish has been granted.
You're going out today.

294
00:26:20.954 --> 00:26:22.581
You're fucking me.

295
00:26:22.831 --> 00:26:25.292
You're taking my place
assisting the 60 gunner.

296
00:26:25.501 --> 00:26:28.670
Sergeant Eversmann said
to get your stuff and get ready.

297
00:26:29.838 --> 00:26:31.799
It's what you wanted, isn't it?

298
00:26:31.965 --> 00:26:33.300
Oh, yeah.

299
00:26:35.094 --> 00:26:36.178
Hell, yeah.

300
00:26:36.345 --> 00:26:40.015
Grimesy, stick with Waddell
and give him ammo when he needs it.

301
00:26:40.099 --> 00:26:41.391
-Hoo-ah?
-Hoo-ah.

302
00:26:41.517 --> 00:26:46.021
I wouldn't worry about that. Generally
speaking, Somalis can't shoot for shit.

303
00:26:46.188 --> 00:26:50.150
Just watch out for the sammys
throwing the rocks, and you'll be fine.

304
00:26:50.359 --> 00:26:51.485
Might even be fun.

305
00:26:51.527 --> 00:26:55.447
D-boys do their thing now.
All we got to do is cover them.

306
00:26:55.531 --> 00:26:58.408
Choppers going to cover us,
and we'll be all right.

307
00:26:59.284 --> 00:27:03.163
Look, you guys,
this is my first time as chalk leader...

308
00:27:03.372 --> 00:27:06.792
...but, this isn't our first time out together.
This is serious.

309
00:27:06.959 --> 00:27:10.379
We're Rangers, not some sorry-ass JROTC.

310
00:27:10.963 --> 00:27:12.214
We're elite.

311
00:27:12.923 --> 00:27:15.050
Let's act like it out there. Hoo-ah?

312
00:27:16.218 --> 00:27:17.886
Any questions?

313
00:27:24.309 --> 00:27:25.978
We're going to be okay.

314
00:27:26.812 --> 00:27:28.647
Grab your gear. Let's move out.

315
00:27:49.001 --> 00:27:53.005
You're not going to need that, dude.
We're not out there long enough.

316
00:28:00.971 --> 00:28:02.389
You won't need that, either.

317
00:28:02.931 --> 00:28:04.808
We'll be back before dark.

318
00:28:05.058 --> 00:28:07.603
You might as well take dope
and beer instead.

319
00:28:07.769 --> 00:28:09.104
What?

320
00:28:09.271 --> 00:28:11.231
Ammo, dude. Take ammo.

321
00:28:18.780 --> 00:28:22.117
Let me tell you something, Grimes.
You got 50 pounds of gear.

322
00:28:22.326 --> 00:28:23.452
You don't need another 12.

323
00:28:23.577 --> 00:28:27.998
I don't know about you,
I don't plan on getting shot running away.

324
00:28:28.081 --> 00:28:29.625
Well, I better keep mine in.

325
00:28:29.791 --> 00:28:30.667
Grimes.

326
00:28:30.918 --> 00:28:32.961
Most important thing:

327
00:28:33.086 --> 00:28:36.340
Remember, when everyone is shooting,
shoot in the same direction.

328
00:28:44.640 --> 00:28:48.310
Look at this.
He's taping his blood type to his boots.

329
00:28:48.477 --> 00:28:52.022
-That's bad luck.
-No, it's smart.

330
00:28:52.314 --> 00:28:54.149
All Delta do that.

331
00:28:54.942 --> 00:28:56.944
That's bad luck too, man.

332
00:28:57.444 --> 00:28:58.570
Come on, let's go.

333
00:29:02.157 --> 00:29:04.993
It's a good thing
you're right-handed, Adonis.

334
00:29:07.120 --> 00:29:11.333
-If not, I don't know what you'd do.
-You're a funny guy, man.

335
00:29:12.960 --> 00:29:15.754
-I'm not taking no death letter.
-We have a deal.

336
00:29:18.548 --> 00:29:20.550
I'll give it to you back in an hour.

337
00:29:20.801 --> 00:29:25.013
-Blackburn, you okay?
-Excited.

338
00:29:26.473 --> 00:29:29.977
In a good way.
I've been training my whole life for this.

339
00:29:30.352 --> 00:29:32.354
You ever shot at anybody before?

340
00:29:32.938 --> 00:29:33.939
No, sir.

341
00:29:35.524 --> 00:29:36.775
Me neither.

342
00:30:11.018 --> 00:30:12.477
Think he's reliable?

343
00:30:12.561 --> 00:30:16.064
Well, we'll see. It's his first time out.

344
00:30:24.156 --> 00:30:26.616
-Tell him to turn his damn radio off.
-Yes, sir.

345
00:30:26.700 --> 00:30:28.535
Tell him to turn his radio off.

346
00:30:28.577 --> 00:30:31.580
Abdi, you need to turn your radio off.

347
00:30:37.919 --> 00:30:42.591
Hi. You've reached Stephanie and Randy,
leave us a message. Thank you.

348
00:30:44.926 --> 00:30:47.346
Hey, baby, it's me. Are you there?

349
00:30:48.930 --> 00:30:50.932
Pick up if you're there.

350
00:30:51.767 --> 00:30:54.770
I'm just calling
to make sure everything's all right.

351
00:30:55.354 --> 00:30:57.773
I'll call you in a couple hours.

352
00:30:58.857 --> 00:31:00.776
You'd better not be sleeping.

353
00:31:01.777 --> 00:31:03.070
Your move, Randy.

354
00:31:04.780 --> 00:31:06.323
I'm missing you.

355
00:31:07.366 --> 00:31:09.117
I love you, baby.

356
00:31:10.577 --> 00:31:11.912
Hello? Hello?

357
00:31:14.122 --> 00:31:15.374
Thanks, bud.

358
00:31:17.751 --> 00:31:19.628
You know, it's kind of funny.

359
00:31:20.253 --> 00:31:23.382
Beautiful beach, beautiful sun.

360
00:31:24.716 --> 00:31:27.010
Could almost be a good place to visit.

361
00:31:27.135 --> 00:31:28.553
Almost.

362
00:31:32.140 --> 00:31:34.309
You don't think we should be here.

363
00:31:35.227 --> 00:31:39.689
You know what I think?
It don't really matter what I think.

364
00:31:41.024 --> 00:31:45.404
Once that first bullet goes past your head,
politics and all that shit...

365
00:31:45.570 --> 00:31:47.697
...just goes right out the window.

366
00:31:48.323 --> 00:31:50.492
I just want to do it right today.

367
00:31:51.159 --> 00:31:54.996
Just watch your corner.
Get all your men back here alive.

368
00:32:20.188 --> 00:32:24.025
Now, is this supposed to be the place,
or did his car just take a dump?

369
00:32:24.234 --> 00:32:25.694
Abdi, come in.

370
00:32:26.194 --> 00:32:28.655
Abdi, can you hear me? Is this the place?

371
00:32:32.993 --> 00:32:34.202
Abdi, come in.

372
00:32:39.499 --> 00:32:42.085
Can you hear me? Abdi.

373
00:32:42.878 --> 00:32:45.881
Abdi, come in. Is this the place?

374
00:32:46.047 --> 00:32:48.550
To my right side, above the cafe.

375
00:32:48.884 --> 00:32:51.178
He says this is the building.

376
00:32:51.386 --> 00:32:52.846
He's certain?

377
00:32:53.430 --> 00:32:55.265
Abdi, you need to be sure.

378
00:32:55.515 --> 00:32:56.892
Are you sure?

379
00:32:58.560 --> 00:33:02.898
Well, it's down the road,
two blocks over on my left.

380
00:33:03.815 --> 00:33:05.734
But there's too many militia.

381
00:33:06.276 --> 00:33:08.612
If I go closer, they might shoot me.

382
00:33:08.987 --> 00:33:12.115
Now he's saying the building's
a couple blocks down...

383
00:33:12.324 --> 00:33:14.701
...but if he's seen outside it, he'll be shot.

384
00:33:15.494 --> 00:33:17.662
I'll fucking shoot him myself.

385
00:33:17.871 --> 00:33:21.416
Tell him I want his skinny ass
parked in front of the building.

386
00:33:21.458 --> 00:33:24.628
He's not getting paid
till he does exactly that.

387
00:33:24.836 --> 00:33:28.048
Three miles to the target.
We're never off the main roads.

388
00:33:28.089 --> 00:33:31.301
At K-four traffic circle, we turn north,
then east on National...

389
00:33:31.384 --> 00:33:34.596
...and we wait until extraction of prisoners
IS complete here.

390
00:33:34.638 --> 00:33:36.598
Then we roll up in force on Hawlwadig...

391
00:33:36.681 --> 00:33:40.227
...load the prisoners, the assault-blocking
forces and bring them back.

392
00:33:40.936 --> 00:33:43.104
Home in an hour. Okay?

393
00:33:43.313 --> 00:33:46.608
There will be some shooting.
Bakara market is the Wild West.

394
00:33:46.691 --> 00:33:49.945
But be careful what you shoot at.
People do live there.

395
00:33:50.570 --> 00:33:51.821
Hoo-ah.

396
00:34:03.792 --> 00:34:07.963
Last one of these guys shot himself
in the head playing Russian roulette.

397
00:34:21.643 --> 00:34:23.979
Sir, the vehicle is stopped.

398
00:34:24.771 --> 00:34:28.149
So this is the real deal now.
He's sure this time.

399
00:34:29.150 --> 00:34:33.280
-He sounds scared shit less.
-Good. That's always a good sign.

400
00:34:44.666 --> 00:34:46.835
That's it. That's our signal.

401
00:34:47.002 --> 00:34:48.336
All right.

402
00:34:48.837 --> 00:34:51.631
All QRF out of the airspace.

403
00:34:53.008 --> 00:34:55.176
All QRF out of the airspace.

404
00:35:00.015 --> 00:35:04.519
All units, Irene. I say again, Irene.

405
00:35:12.027 --> 00:35:16.615
Check in when ready. Barber 51 up
and ready. Star 41 up and ready.

406
00:35:16.865 --> 00:35:18.074
Irene!

407
00:35:18.742 --> 00:35:20.201
Copy, Irene.

408
00:35:21.077 --> 00:35:22.370
Fucking Irene!

409
00:35:36.259 --> 00:35:37.093
Come on.

410
00:35:43.850 --> 00:35:45.018
Good luck, boys.

411
00:35:45.060 --> 00:35:46.519
Be careful.

412
00:35:46.895 --> 00:35:49.022
No one gets left behind.

413
00:35:50.899 --> 00:35:52.233
What's wrong?

414
00:35:53.068 --> 00:35:56.237
Nothing. He's just never done that before.

415
00:35:57.238 --> 00:35:58.740
Aw, fuck!

416
00:36:02.869 --> 00:36:04.037
Let's go.

417
00:36:05.038 --> 00:36:07.791
Sergeant Struecker. Let's roll.

418
00:38:46.991 --> 00:38:48.326
Two minutes.

419
00:38:49.494 --> 00:38:50.912
Two minutes.

420
00:39:36.082 --> 00:39:38.668
Why are they burning tires?

421
00:39:38.960 --> 00:39:41.796
Signals to the militia that we're coming!

422
00:39:43.965 --> 00:39:47.302
Okay, 56, looks like there's some friendlies
on the ground.

423
00:39:47.468 --> 00:39:50.471
Looks like I've got a tally on the voice.

424
00:39:56.978 --> 00:39:58.271
One minute.

425
00:39:59.647 --> 00:40:00.857
One minute.

426
00:40:05.278 --> 00:40:06.613
What's that for?

427
00:40:07.906 --> 00:40:10.867
Last rope, I almost bit my tongue off.

428
00:40:42.398 --> 00:40:43.775
Touching base.

429
00:40:47.612 --> 00:40:49.530
Two feet, one foot...

430
00:40:51.032 --> 00:40:52.367
...clear.

431
00:40:53.451 --> 00:40:56.454
Little birds touching down at target.

432
00:41:41.040 --> 00:41:42.083
Ropes!

433
00:41:43.376 --> 00:41:45.878
Go! Go! Go!

434
00:41:52.927 --> 00:41:56.597
Chalk One troops are on the deck.
Chalk Two deployed.

435
00:41:56.764 --> 00:42:00.101
This is McKnight.
Uniform 64 approaching staging area.

436
00:42:11.821 --> 00:42:13.406
Down! Get down!

437
00:42:13.614 --> 00:42:15.366
Down! Stay down!

438
00:42:15.575 --> 00:42:17.285
Get down! Everybody down!

439
00:42:17.368 --> 00:42:18.786
You, down!

440
00:42:18.995 --> 00:42:20.038
Get down!

441
00:42:20.121 --> 00:42:21.122
On the floor.

442
00:42:27.462 --> 00:42:28.921
Let's go, let's go!

443
00:42:30.298 --> 00:42:32.675
Grimesy! No fear!

444
00:42:32.925 --> 00:42:34.761
Oh, yeah, right!

445
00:42:38.473 --> 00:42:41.309
Rangers securing perimeter. Four corners.

446
00:42:41.642 --> 00:42:44.270
Colonel, they're shooting at us!

447
00:42:44.937 --> 00:42:46.939
Colonel, they're shooting at us!

448
00:42:46.981 --> 00:42:48.316
Well, shoot back!

449
00:42:52.153 --> 00:42:55.239
This is 64. Chalks on the ground,
going into holding pattern.

450
00:42:55.323 --> 00:42:58.117
This is 62, delivered chalks.
Going to cover pattern.

451
00:42:58.159 --> 00:43:02.288
Super 62, take up an overhead pattern
to provide sniper cover. Over.

452
00:43:02.455 --> 00:43:05.833
This is Super 65. Chalks on the ground,
going into holding pattern.

453
00:43:11.839 --> 00:43:15.176
Go, Blackburn, go! Go!

454
00:43:15.510 --> 00:43:16.761
Go, Blackburn!

455
00:43:19.263 --> 00:43:20.473
RPG!

456
00:43:20.681 --> 00:43:22.141
Hold on!

457
00:43:25.103 --> 00:43:26.312
No!

458
00:43:36.781 --> 00:43:38.825
C-2, we got a man fallen.

459
00:43:39.408 --> 00:43:41.911
Super-61, you're a sitting duck.

460
00:43:42.328 --> 00:43:45.540
Take up overhead pattern
to provide sniper cover. Over.

461
00:43:45.748 --> 00:43:48.042
Roger that. 61 coming out.

462
00:43:49.252 --> 00:43:53.589
13, go ahead. I need you to move to
the north of the street.

463
00:43:53.840 --> 00:43:56.425
Right to the north. Right there. Over.

464
00:43:57.718 --> 00:43:59.512
Doc! Doc Schmid!

465
00:43:59.887 --> 00:44:01.264
Come on!

466
00:44:01.514 --> 00:44:04.058
Schmid, we got a man hit.

467
00:44:06.018 --> 00:44:08.938
-Where's he hit?
-He's not. He fell.

468
00:44:09.021 --> 00:44:10.982
-What?
-He fell.

469
00:44:14.235 --> 00:44:16.028
Why aren't you shooting?

470
00:44:16.237 --> 00:44:18.072
We're not being shot at yet!

471
00:44:18.281 --> 00:44:19.699
How can you tell?

472
00:44:19.866 --> 00:44:21.450
A hiss means it's close.

473
00:44:21.534 --> 00:44:22.952
A snap means--

474
00:44:23.202 --> 00:44:24.996
Now they're shooting at us!

475
00:44:33.754 --> 00:44:34.964
Galentine!

476
00:44:38.801 --> 00:44:41.429
Get me Captain Steele!
Get me Captain Steele!

477
00:44:41.804 --> 00:44:45.099
Juliet 64, this is Juliet 25. Come in. Over.

478
00:44:45.266 --> 00:44:47.101
Blackburn, can you hear me?

479
00:44:47.268 --> 00:44:50.438
Juliet 64, this is 25. Come in. Over.

480
00:44:50.730 --> 00:44:52.148
I can't get him!

481
00:44:53.149 --> 00:44:56.652
Juliet 64, this is Chalk Four!
We've got a man down!

482
00:44:56.777 --> 00:44:58.779
We need to get him out of here! Over.

483
00:44:58.821 --> 00:45:01.949
This is 64. Say again, 25. Over.

484
00:45:02.700 --> 00:45:05.203
We've got a man down! Over.

485
00:45:06.787 --> 00:45:09.957
Take a breath, 25, and calm down. Over.

486
00:45:10.458 --> 00:45:13.127
-Man down!
-Missed that, 25.

487
00:45:13.211 --> 00:45:15.046
-Fuck it.
-Say again.

488
00:45:15.129 --> 00:45:17.340
Matt, it's a long way to the humvees!

489
00:45:17.423 --> 00:45:20.801
We'll get a stretcher in here.
Get him to the target building.

490
00:45:21.052 --> 00:45:22.428
What did he say?

491
00:45:22.637 --> 00:45:26.474
Super 61,
we got a man wounded on the ground.

492
00:45:27.308 --> 00:45:30.228
-Stretcher!
-Get me a stretcher!

493
00:45:30.478 --> 00:45:32.313
Come on. Stretcher.

494
00:45:32.480 --> 00:45:33.814
Come on, come on!

495
00:45:34.732 --> 00:45:36.317
Grab this end!

496
00:45:37.652 --> 00:45:39.320
Let's go!

497
00:45:40.154 --> 00:45:42.114
-All right.
-Go.

498
00:45:42.406 --> 00:45:44.867
Get him to the humvees.
We'll hold down the corner.

499
00:45:44.951 --> 00:45:46.744
Up to the humvees! Now!

500
00:45:50.331 --> 00:45:52.500
