01:13:04.964 --> 01:13:08.801
No, we're good. Got a slight vibration
in the pedals, but we're good.

759
01:13:09.635 --> 01:13:13.973
All right, put her down on the airfield, 64.
Have it checked out just to be safe.

760
01:13:14.473 --> 01:13:15.474
Roger.

761
01:13:18.144 --> 01:13:22.315
I'm getting movement in these pedals.
Check the systems again.

762
01:13:37.496 --> 01:13:39.999
We lost the tail rotor! It's gone!

763
01:13:40.166 --> 01:13:41.834
64 is going down!

764
01:13:43.002 --> 01:13:44.503
64 is going in hard.

765
01:13:46.339 --> 01:13:48.090
64 going down.

766
01:13:53.012 --> 01:13:54.847
We're going down.

767
01:13:59.852 --> 01:14:01.729
Get Struecker's column back out there.

768
01:14:01.812 --> 01:14:04.106
They need to get to
Durant's crash site fast.

769
01:14:04.190 --> 01:14:06.817
-Another bird down.
- I want them out of there.

770
01:14:07.526 --> 01:14:08.486
All of them.

771
01:14:12.823 --> 01:14:15.952
Captain Steele, we got to move
or we'll get pinned down!

772
01:14:16.202 --> 01:14:18.204
We're moving as fast as we can.

773
01:14:18.329 --> 01:14:21.499
You let me do my job and you do yours.
Over.

774
01:14:30.132 --> 01:14:32.635
-Fuck! Fuck!
-Ruiz stay down.

775
01:14:32.718 --> 01:14:33.886
-I fucking knew--
-Medic.

776
01:14:33.928 --> 01:14:37.723
Fuck this! Captain Steele,
I'll take out the threat in the window.

777
01:14:37.974 --> 01:14:40.226
We'll rally at the gray building.
Coming through.

778
01:14:40.309 --> 01:14:40.851
Sarg'nt!

779
01:14:41.060 --> 01:14:42.228
All right, let's move!

780
01:14:48.067 --> 01:14:49.402
Cover me!

781
01:14:55.241 --> 01:14:57.910
-Let's go, let's move!
-Moving out.

782
01:15:03.582 --> 01:15:04.125
Friendly!

783
01:15:04.208 --> 01:15:05.918
Friendlies coming through!

784
01:15:06.002 --> 01:15:08.379
Let's go, let's go! Move up!

785
01:15:08.587 --> 01:15:10.506
Come on, come on!

786
01:15:11.007 --> 01:15:12.049
Come on!

787
01:15:19.724 --> 01:15:21.434
Move up! Go! Move up!

788
01:15:21.809 --> 01:15:23.561
What the fuck are you doing out there?

789
01:15:23.602 --> 01:15:26.313
Doing my job!
We got to get to that crash site!

790
01:15:26.647 --> 01:15:29.442
We got to get on that street,
and we got to move!

791
01:15:29.900 --> 01:15:31.986
And you have got to keep up, sir!

792
01:15:32.153 --> 01:15:34.321
Don't you ever give me orders, Sergeant.

793
01:15:34.405 --> 01:15:36.866
We are combat ineffective, understand?

794
01:15:37.450 --> 01:15:38.993
We got too many wounded to move!

795
01:15:39.076 --> 01:15:42.288
Then give me some shooters
and I'll circle us to the bird.

796
01:15:44.999 --> 01:15:47.501
Grimes! You're with Chalk Four?

797
01:15:47.668 --> 01:15:48.711
Yes, sir!

798
01:15:48.919 --> 01:15:52.339
All right, hook up with Delta!
Rejoin with Sergeant Eversmann.

799
01:15:52.923 --> 01:15:55.176
The rest of you, secure this position!

800
01:15:55.384 --> 01:15:57.636
Treat the wounded,
we'll wait for the convoy!

801
01:15:57.678 --> 01:16:00.222
Then we'll rally at the crash site. Roger!

802
01:16:00.431 --> 01:16:01.807
My guys, let's go!

803
01:16:32.713 --> 01:16:35.716
C-2, I have two Delta snipers,
Shughart and Gordon...

804
01:16:35.800 --> 01:16:38.511
...volunteering to secure crash site two.
Over.

805
01:16:39.136 --> 01:16:43.307
No, Super 62, negative that request.
Can't risk another bird.

806
01:16:45.142 --> 01:16:49.063
We don't see anything moving down there,
we don't even know if anyone's alive.

807
01:16:50.356 --> 01:16:53.067
A ground team is being organized
to go in now.

808
01:16:53.234 --> 01:16:54.985
ETA on ground team? Over.

809
01:16:55.152 --> 01:16:58.239
Unknown, not long.

810
01:16:58.405 --> 01:17:00.741
Do what you can from the air.

811
01:17:04.745 --> 01:17:06.539
All right, gather around!

812
01:17:06.664 --> 01:17:09.875
Durant's 64 is down.
We're going back in to get him!

813
01:17:09.959 --> 01:17:12.086
That's crazy. Is there anyone alive?

814
01:17:12.169 --> 01:17:14.547
Doesn't matter, no one gets left behind.

815
01:17:14.797 --> 01:17:17.007
We're wasting time here.

816
01:17:17.174 --> 01:17:20.219
Refit and max out ammo and grenades,
you got five!

817
01:17:21.428 --> 01:17:23.264
Sizemore, where are you going?

818
01:17:23.347 --> 01:17:26.183
-With you guys.
-Not with that cast on you're not.

819
01:17:27.059 --> 01:17:30.354
All right, all right, all right.
Go get your k-pot.

820
01:17:32.606 --> 01:17:33.816
Talk to me.

821
01:17:34.108 --> 01:17:35.484
I can't go back out there.

822
01:17:35.568 --> 01:17:40.114
Thomas, everyone feels
the same way you do. All right?

823
01:17:40.322 --> 01:17:43.534
It's what you do right now
that makes a difference.

824
01:17:44.577 --> 01:17:46.078
It's your call.

825
01:17:46.495 --> 01:17:47.580
Hoo-ah?

826
01:17:53.752 --> 01:17:54.962
Hoo-ah.

827
01:18:11.312 --> 01:18:14.940
It'll probably help to wash
the blood out of the humvees.

828
01:18:23.949 --> 01:18:25.868
Sergeant Struecker!

829
01:18:26.535 --> 01:18:29.872
Sergeant Struecker! Can I go, Sarge?

830
01:18:30.289 --> 01:18:32.208
-You got some ammo?
-Roger, Sarge!

831
01:18:32.374 --> 01:18:33.959
Hop in!

832
01:18:51.977 --> 01:18:53.354
Wait!

833
01:18:54.313 --> 01:18:56.482
Let's go, Thomas. Get in!

834
01:19:20.256 --> 01:19:21.423
Which way?

835
01:19:26.428 --> 01:19:29.431
-That way, I think!
-Not so fucking loud.

836
01:20:03.215 --> 01:20:04.550
Nice donkey.

837
01:20:23.152 --> 01:20:24.570
Rangers?

838
01:20:25.070 --> 01:20:26.071
Who?

839
01:20:26.905 --> 01:20:30.451
It's Yurek! You fucking assholes!

840
01:20:30.617 --> 01:20:32.036
Fuck!

841
01:20:32.244 --> 01:20:34.788
Dude, we almost fucking killed you!

842
01:20:35.039 --> 01:20:38.125
-Come to us!
-Fuck you, come to me.

843
01:20:50.596 --> 01:20:51.930
Sorry, Sarge!

844
01:20:52.097 --> 01:20:54.016
Dude, where the fuck have you been?

845
01:20:54.099 --> 01:20:55.934
Never mind, you brought NOD, right?

846
01:20:56.018 --> 01:20:58.354
No, I didn't and you want to know why?

847
01:20:58.437 --> 01:21:01.774
Because you said: "You won't need that,
we'll be back in a half-hour."

848
01:21:01.857 --> 01:21:03.442
Well, I wasn't saying it to you.

849
01:21:03.484 --> 01:21:05.486
Nelson, cover this way.

850
01:21:05.861 --> 01:21:07.446
We'll need night vision.

851
01:21:07.529 --> 01:21:09.948
What's the matter with you?

852
01:21:10.282 --> 01:21:13.077
Oh, he's deaf. It's my fault.

853
01:21:13.369 --> 01:21:15.621
-We need to get out of here!
-That way.

854
01:21:15.704 --> 01:21:19.375
We can't be far from the crash.
Which way?

855
01:21:20.042 --> 01:21:21.794
I thought you might know.

856
01:21:22.503 --> 01:21:23.962
Let's move out.

857
01:21:29.510 --> 01:21:32.096
Nelson, Twombly? Come in. Over.

858
01:21:33.138 --> 01:21:37.351
Nelson, Twombly, this is Galentine.
We need a position of the convoy. Over.

859
01:21:38.394 --> 01:21:40.646
I can't raise them, Sergeant.

860
01:21:40.896 --> 01:21:43.565
Sir, let's get the fuck out of here and evac!

861
01:21:45.025 --> 01:21:48.112
-Let's move out.
-Back to the stronghold!

862
01:21:48.320 --> 01:21:49.321
Come on!

863
01:21:51.615 --> 01:21:54.827
Ground forces have occupied
several buildings along Marehan Road...

864
01:21:54.910 --> 01:21:56.620
...but they're all spread out.

865
01:21:56.662 --> 01:22:01.125
Eversmann's Chalk Four has set up
a perimeter around Wolcott's crash site.

866
01:22:01.333 --> 01:22:03.669
DiTomasso is in the adjacent structure.

867
01:22:04.044 --> 01:22:08.006
Captain Steele and about 40 men, Rangers,
are here, a couple blocks away.

868
01:22:08.048 --> 01:22:09.591
They're banged up pretty bad.

869
01:22:09.675 --> 01:22:14.513
He set up a casualty collection point,
I don't think they'll be able to move.

870
01:22:14.763 --> 01:22:17.266
Sergeant Sanderson
and a small Delta team...

871
01:22:17.349 --> 01:22:21.186
...are moving from Steele's position
to the crash site as we speak.

872
01:22:32.197 --> 01:22:33.365
Draw off fire!

873
01:22:33.449 --> 01:22:36.535
When this asshole stops to reload,
cover me!

874
01:22:36.702 --> 01:22:38.162
-Go!
-Sir.

875
01:22:41.665 --> 01:22:42.624
Again!

876
01:22:47.713 --> 01:22:49.214
Loading!

877
01:22:51.550 --> 01:22:53.051
Keep going!

878
01:22:53.802 --> 01:22:55.554
I'm jammed!

879
01:22:56.722 --> 01:22:58.182
I got it!

880
01:22:59.391 --> 01:23:01.185
No, shit!

881
01:23:13.739 --> 01:23:15.032
RPG!

882
01:23:29.963 --> 01:23:32.549
You all right? You okay?

883
01:23:32.716 --> 01:23:35.677
Yeah. I can hear bells ringing.

884
01:23:37.262 --> 01:23:39.515
Come on! Come on!

885
01:23:41.266 --> 01:23:42.267
Go!

886
01:23:49.441 --> 01:23:52.444
A crowd is advancing six,
seven blocks from the crash.

887
01:23:52.528 --> 01:23:54.821
Shughart and Gordon
again request permission...

888
01:23:54.905 --> 01:23:58.325
...to secure until convoy arrives. Over.

889
01:23:58.534 --> 01:24:01.620
General, crowds are in the hundreds now.

890
01:24:01.828 --> 01:24:05.290
From where they are,
they can see things clearer than any of us.

891
01:24:05.415 --> 01:24:07.292
They know what they're asking.

892
01:24:07.501 --> 01:24:08.961
Let me talk to them.

893
01:24:09.169 --> 01:24:10.295
This is Garrison.

894
01:24:10.337 --> 01:24:14.633
I want to make sure that you understand
what you're asking, so say it out loud.

895
01:24:16.677 --> 01:24:20.681
We're asking to go in and set up
a perimeter until ground support arrives.

896
01:24:21.014 --> 01:24:25.185
You realize that I cannot tell you
when that might be, it could take a while.

897
01:24:26.103 --> 01:24:28.647
-Roger that.
-You still want to go in there?

898
01:24:28.981 --> 01:24:29.773
Yes, sir.

899
01:24:33.777 --> 01:24:35.404
-Colonel Harrell?
-Yes, General?

900
01:24:35.487 --> 01:24:36.530
It's your call.

901
01:24:37.698 --> 01:24:39.199
Roger that.

902
01:24:40.993 --> 01:24:43.161
Goffena, put them in.

903
01:24:57.092 --> 01:24:58.844
Motherfucker. Motherfucker.

904
01:25:04.016 --> 01:25:05.017
RPG!

905
01:25:14.901 --> 01:25:16.528
Set up your perimeter!

906
01:25:23.952 --> 01:25:25.954
There's a fucking rocket in him, sir!

907
01:25:26.038 --> 01:25:29.875
Othic, calm down, goddamn it!
There's live ordnance, now get out!

908
01:25:31.209 --> 01:25:33.045
Son of a bitch.

909
01:25:34.546 --> 01:25:37.716
All right, lift him up!
Lift him up! Easy, easy!

910
01:25:38.008 --> 01:25:41.094
All right, get him in there! Good, good!
Easy, easy!

911
01:25:42.304 --> 01:25:43.847
Get in that truck and drive.

912
01:25:43.889 --> 01:25:45.974
-But I'm shot, Colonel.
-Everybody's shot.

913
01:25:46.058 --> 01:25:48.143
We need the prisoners! Let's go!

914
01:25:49.227 --> 01:25:52.731
Surveillance says to take Hawlwadig,
then go straight.

915
01:25:52.939 --> 01:25:57.235
McKnight, we need you to turn around
and head back to Hawlwadig.

916
01:25:57.402 --> 01:25:59.655
You're shitting me!
We just came through there!

917
01:25:59.738 --> 01:26:01.490
There must be a better route!

918
01:26:01.573 --> 01:26:06.745
That's the info I'm getting from JOC,
you need to turn around and head back.

919
01:26:07.996 --> 01:26:10.040
Roger that. Roger that.

920
01:26:10.499 --> 01:26:13.377
I cannot believe this shit!
Turn us around, Maddox.

921
01:26:13.418 --> 01:26:15.420
They're trying to get us fucking killed!

922
01:26:15.462 --> 01:26:17.089
Just get it over with! Drive!

923
01:26:17.130 --> 01:26:18.131
Goddamn!

924
01:26:18.423 --> 01:26:20.759
Get us out of here, goddamn it, drive!

925
01:26:28.433 --> 01:26:29.893
Keep your foot on the gas!

926
01:26:29.935 --> 01:26:32.187
Keep your foot on the gas!

927
01:26:43.699 --> 01:26:44.783
Fuck!

928
01:26:47.703 --> 01:26:48.704
Shit.

929
01:27:04.136 --> 01:27:06.930
C-2, Shughart and Gordon
are on the deck. Over.

930
01:27:07.139 --> 01:27:08.098
Roger.

931
01:27:34.166 --> 01:27:35.751
Friendlies!

932
01:27:37.919 --> 01:27:39.171
God, it's good to see you!

933
01:27:39.212 --> 01:27:41.173
It's good to see you. How bad?

934
01:27:41.256 --> 01:27:44.176
My leg's broken
and my back feels kind of weird.

935
01:27:44.301 --> 01:27:46.386
We've got to get you out of here.

936
01:27:47.345 --> 01:27:49.181
I'm pulling him out! Cover!

937
01:27:52.601 --> 01:27:53.602
Wait, I--

938
01:28:02.152 --> 01:28:03.403
I'm putting you down.

939
01:28:03.653 --> 01:28:06.573
C-2, we're at the 64 crash site,
securing perimeter.

940
01:28:06.656 --> 01:28:08.241
-You all right?
-Yeah, I'm good.

941
01:28:08.325 --> 01:28:09.743
You're locked and loaded.

942
01:28:09.826 --> 01:28:13.538
Any skinnies come around these corners,
you watch our backs.

943
01:28:13.622 --> 01:28:16.291
-Where's the rescue squad?
-We're it.

944
01:28:22.005 --> 01:28:25.091
All right, stop, stop, Maddox. Stop.

945
01:28:26.092 --> 01:28:27.552
Son of a bitch.

946
01:28:27.677 --> 01:28:30.555
Romeo 64, we're back where we started.

947
01:28:30.764 --> 01:28:33.475
I'm low on ammo,
I got many wounded including me...

948
01:28:33.558 --> 01:28:35.519
...vehicles that are barely running.

949
01:28:35.560 --> 01:28:38.522
Okay, Danny,
I need a no-b.s. assessment here.

950
01:28:38.939 --> 01:28:41.066
Can you get to the crash site?

951
01:28:41.817 --> 01:28:44.402
Colonel, I can't see shit.

952
01:28:48.490 --> 01:28:49.407
Negative.

953
01:28:49.449 --> 01:28:52.536
With the amount of wounded we have,
we'd do more harm than good.

954
01:28:52.577 --> 01:28:56.581
We need to come back to base, rearm
and regroup and then we can go back out.

955
01:28:56.623 --> 01:28:57.624
Roger.

956
01:28:59.459 --> 01:29:02.754
C-2, bring them back.
Get them out of there.

957
01:29:04.214 --> 01:29:05.799
Roger. Return to base.

958
01:29:06.591 --> 01:29:07.968
We're going home!

959
01:29:08.176 --> 01:29:10.178
Let's go. Left.

960
01:29:23.108 --> 01:29:26.403
Roger that. Understand.
Convoy returning to base.

961
01:29:31.658 --> 01:29:33.785
-What's up?
-They're sending them back.

962
01:29:33.827 --> 01:29:35.495
The convoy's headed back to base camp.

963
01:29:35.579 --> 01:29:37.747
Oh, now that makes sense, don't it?

964
01:29:38.248 --> 01:29:42.294
We need to exfil the wounded now
and get out of here before it's too late!

965
01:29:42.627 --> 01:29:46.172
If Colonel McKnight went back to base,
then he had a good reason.

966
01:29:46.339 --> 01:29:47.799
It changes nothing.

967
01:29:48.008 --> 01:29:49.426
All right, listen up.

968
01:29:49.467 --> 01:29:53.471
We're going to hold the perimeter
and we're going to hold the strong point.

969
01:29:54.264 --> 01:29:57.517
Conserve your ammo.
Only shoot at what you can hit.

970
01:29:59.311 --> 01:30:01.146
The convoy is going to come.

971
01:30:02.522 --> 01:30:03.523
We're going to get home.

972
01:30:15.994 --> 01:30:16.995
Loading!

973
01:30:25.503 --> 01:30:26.838
Loading!

974
01:30:27.339 --> 01:30:29.174
Randy, I need a pistol mag!

975
01:30:42.520 --> 01:30:43.521
Loading!

976
01:30:47.275 --> 01:30:48.693
Randy, last mag!

977
01:30:52.197 --> 01:30:53.198
Gordy!

978
01:30:56.952 --> 01:30:57.953
Fuck!

979
01:31:11.424 --> 01:31:13.635
Gordy is gone, man. I'll be outside.

980
01:31:14.219 --> 01:31:15.345
Good luck.

981
01:31:36.741 --> 01:31:39.619
We need the 10th Mountain in there.
Everything they got.

982
01:31:39.703 --> 01:31:42.831
Pakistanis, Malays,
I want their tanks and APCs.

983
01:31:43.456 --> 01:31:44.874
They don't know we've gone in.

984
01:31:44.916 --> 01:31:49.379
We have stirred up a hornet's nest here.
We're fighting the entire city.

985
01:31:49.879 --> 01:31:54.551
I want every vehicle possible that's got
4 wheels and armor. Get everything.

986
01:31:54.759 --> 01:31:58.054
Once they've assembled, we'll move
our men out of the hostile area...

987
01:31:58.096 --> 01:32:00.724
...and back to the Pakistani Stadium,
the safe zone.

988
01:32:00.765 --> 01:32:03.309
-Now, let's go.
-Roger that.

989
01:34:40.175 --> 01:34:42.802
On your knees! Get down! Get down!

990
01:34:47.432 --> 01:34:51.394
Stay with me.
You just got a bullet in the leg.

991
01:34:55.940 --> 01:34:58.860
See where those tires are burning?
All that black smoke?

992
01:34:58.943 --> 01:35:02.447
Roger. I can see it,
but I can't get there. Over.

993
01:35:02.655 --> 01:35:05.742
Go 100 meters past it. That's the crash.

994
01:35:05.950 --> 01:35:08.077
Negative. You don't understand.

995
01:35:08.244 --> 01:35:12.790
It's roadblock after roadblock.
You have to find us another route. Over.

996
01:35:13.416 --> 01:35:17.045
There ain't one. The only other route is
all the way around the city.

997
01:35:17.128 --> 01:35:18.213
Roger that.

998
01:35:18.296 --> 01:35:20.798
Kilo 64, this is Kilo 11.

999
01:35:21.007 --> 01:35:25.470
Request permission to move
to crash site number two on foot. Over.

1000
01:35:26.387 --> 01:35:28.431
Green light, Kilo 11.

1001
01:35:28.473 --> 01:35:30.892
Stop the vehicle. Let me out.

1002
01:36:15.979 --> 01:36:19.565
After I'm finished with this,
I'll whip you boys up some margaritas.

1003
01:36:19.649 --> 01:36:22.527
The usual. Blended, no salt.

1004
01:36:29.701 --> 01:36:32.912
This is Kilo 12.
We've got to change our position. Over.

1005
01:36:46.718 --> 01:36:48.428
Eversmann, come in.

1006
01:36:48.678 --> 01:36:49.762
Eversmann.

1007
01:36:52.223 --> 01:36:54.559
-Roger who is this?
-Sanderson.

1008
01:36:54.600 --> 01:36:59.063
Do not-- I say again, do not fire to the
east. We are coming to you.

1009
01:37:00.523 --> 01:37:01.649
Understood.

1010
01:37:01.899 --> 01:37:04.360
DiTomasso and his men
are on the southeast corner.

1011
01:37:04.402 --> 01:37:06.779
We need you on the northeast building.

1012
01:37:06.863 --> 01:37:08.323
Roger. We'll take it.

1013
01:37:08.906 --> 01:37:11.159
Watch out for skinnies.
They're on the rooftops.

1014
01:37:11.242 --> 01:37:13.745
They're in prayer but not for much longer.

1015
01:37:17.206 --> 01:37:19.000
Hold your fire to the east.

1016
01:37:41.105 --> 01:37:42.774
Eversmann? It's Yurek.

1017
01:37:43.149 --> 01:37:45.568
I got Nelson and Twombly with me.

1018
01:37:45.943 --> 01:37:48.738
We got the chopper in sight.
Where are you?

1019
01:37:48.946 --> 01:37:52.116
We're on the southwest corner.
Where have you been? Are you okay?

1020
01:37:52.158 --> 01:37:53.034
Yeah.

1021
01:37:54.619 --> 01:37:56.746
Hold your fire. We're coming in.

1022
01:38:01.542 --> 01:38:02.627
We got to go.

1023
01:38:02.668 --> 01:38:05.630
Shawn, listen!
Sergeant Yurek's going to run first.

1024
01:38:05.797 --> 01:38:09.759
When he gets across the street,
he'll turn around and cover you as you run.

1025
01:38:09.801 --> 01:38:13.971
Listen closely. When you get there,
you'll turn around and cover me, okay?

1026
01:38:15.598 --> 01:38:17.934
You won't just run
to Eversmann's position.

1027
01:38:17.975 --> 01:38:20.812
You're going to stop
and you are going to cover me.

1028
01:38:21.312 --> 01:38:23.481
It's important you understand that.

1029
01:38:23.981 --> 01:38:25.316
Okay, you ready?

1030
01:38:26.150 --> 01:38:27.485
Yeah, I guess.

1031
01:38:33.074 --> 01:38:34.659
-Don't forget.
-What?

1032
01:38:35.326 --> 01:38:36.536
Don't forget.

1033
01:38:50.049 --> 01:38:53.428
I got them in my sight, Sarg'nt.
They're coming up on the west gate.

1034
01:38:53.511 --> 01:38:54.637
I see them.

1035
01:38:57.557 --> 01:38:58.850
Let's move out.

1036
01:39:01.310 --> 01:39:03.020
Can you cover us, Sergeant?

1037
01:39:03.271 --> 01:39:04.605
We got you.

1038
01:39:11.863 --> 01:39:13.239
Nelson!

1039
01:39:20.037 --> 01:39:21.038
Fuck!

1040
01:39:29.547 --> 01:39:30.548
Twombly!

1041
01:39:32.383 --> 01:39:33.509
Smith! No!

1042
01:39:33.634 --> 01:39:34.886
You all right?

1043
01:39:38.222 --> 01:39:39.599
Get it off of me!

1044
01:39:40.391 --> 01:39:41.767
Get it off!

1045
01:39:43.060 --> 01:39:44.729
Come on, man. Come on.

1046
01:39:45.897 --> 01:39:48.816
Doc! Need some help with Smith here!

1047
01:39:57.241 --> 01:39:58.534
My leg! My leg!

1048
01:39:58.576 --> 01:40:00.286
Come on, Jamie, I got you!

1049
01:40:07.376 --> 01:40:09.420
Up, one, two, three.

1050
01:40:10.755 --> 01:40:13.424
-You're all right.
-I need some pressure on this wound.

1051
01:40:13.466 --> 01:40:14.550
My right thigh!

1052
01:40:14.592 --> 01:40:16.302
Pressure, yeah.

1053
01:40:16.469 --> 01:40:18.804
-Are my balls okay?
-You still have your balls.

1054
01:40:18.888 --> 01:40:19.972
I need more men in here.

1055
01:40:20.056 --> 01:40:22.642
Twombly! Nelson!

1056
01:40:22.725 --> 01:40:25.770
-Put him down.
-Oh, man, that really....

1057
01:40:27.104 --> 01:40:29.357
- It really hurts!
-Direct pressure on that.

1058
01:40:29.440 --> 01:40:30.942
It's okay, it's okay.

1059
01:40:31.484 --> 01:40:33.861
-Let me see it!
-All right.

1060
01:40:34.320 --> 01:40:36.614
All right, let me get a look at that.

1061
01:40:36.989 --> 01:40:38.407
Oh, shit!

1062
01:40:38.616 --> 01:40:39.825
Oh, fuck!

1063
01:40:40.034 --> 01:40:42.453
-What the fuck was that?
-It's all right.

1064
01:40:42.495 --> 01:40:44.664
Hold that down. I need a medivac now.

1065
01:40:44.747 --> 01:40:46.123
Fuck. Galentine!

1066
01:40:46.332 --> 01:40:47.333
It's all right.

1067
01:40:47.416 --> 01:40:49.210
Galentine! Get me Captain Steele!

1068
01:40:50.127 --> 01:40:53.172
-Sarg'nt Ruiz, how you doing?
-Juliet 64, come in. Over.

1069
01:40:53.256 --> 01:40:57.134
They're not going to come and get us.
They're not going to come for us.

1070
01:40:57.218 --> 01:41:00.304
I need you to suck it up, Sarg'nt.
I need you to focus.

1071
01:41:00.346 --> 01:41:02.765
-Can you do that?
-Juliet 64, come in. Over.

1072
01:41:02.807 --> 01:41:04.725
Now, can you hold your weapon?

1073
01:41:05.101 --> 01:41:06.102
Yes, sir.

1074
01:41:06.310 --> 01:41:10.314
Anybody comes through that door
gets two in the chest and one in the head.

1075
01:41:10.648 --> 01:41:14.110
-You understand?
-I'm still in the fight, sir.

1076
01:41:14.360 --> 01:41:17.321
Captain Steele,
I need a medivac in here now!

1077
01:41:17.488 --> 01:41:19.991
-Corporal Smith has been hit!
-Hold on, 25.

1078
01:41:20.324 --> 01:41:21.784
Still in the fight.

1079
01:41:21.826 --> 01:41:23.327
He's hurt pretty bad.

1080
01:41:23.369 --> 01:41:27.123
25, we got wounded too. You'll have to
maintain your situation, over.

1081
01:41:27.164 --> 01:41:29.750
If he doesn't get help in a half-hour,
he's in trouble!

1082
01:41:30.501 --> 01:41:32.628
C-2, this is 64.

1083
01:41:32.837 --> 01:41:37.049
Requesting a medivac for a critically
wounded at Chalk Four's location. Over.

1084
01:41:37.133 --> 01:41:40.011
Command, Chalk Four
is requesting medivac.

1085
01:41:40.177 --> 01:41:42.513
Can't risk it. It's still too hot.

1086
01:41:43.014 --> 01:41:47.852
Captain, we cannot send in medivac
at this time. Sit tight. Over.

1087
01:41:48.185 --> 01:41:52.023
25, this is 64. Negative on the medivac.
It's not possible.

1088
01:41:52.231 --> 01:41:56.027
JOC cannot risk another bird.
You'll just have to hold on.

1089
01:42:02.575 --> 01:42:04.035
All right. I got him.

1090
01:42:04.076 --> 01:42:06.537
I want direct pressure on the wound.

1091
01:42:08.372 --> 01:42:10.207
It's going to be all right.

1092
01:42:54.752 --> 01:42:57.922
This is Kilo 11.
I'm at the Durant crash site.

1093
01:42:58.089 --> 01:42:59.507
Roger that.

1094
01:43:21.112 --> 01:43:22.863
Crash site two secured.

1095
01:43:23.114 --> 01:43:25.449
Lieutenant Colonel Cribbs for you, sir.

1096
01:43:25.950 --> 01:43:26.826
Cribbs?

1097
01:43:28.828 --> 01:43:31.122
-They're still debating the route.
-How long?

1098
01:43:31.288 --> 01:43:32.915
At least a couple of hours.

1099
01:43:33.082 --> 01:43:34.750
We haven't got that long, Joe.

1100
01:43:34.792 --> 01:43:39.422
Pakistani General says, since
we didn't deign to inform him of the raid...

1101
01:43:39.630 --> 01:43:43.467
...it'll take some time to mobilize
the 10th Mountain and 100 vehicles.

1102
01:43:43.509 --> 01:43:45.511
You tell the general this:

1103
01:43:45.720 --> 01:43:48.639
I understand,
but it is my duty to remind him...

1104
01:43:48.806 --> 01:43:52.893
...that my men are surrounded
by thousands of armed Somali militia.

1105
01:43:53.102 --> 01:43:58.357
It's imperative that we move them out
of the hostile area and into the safe zone.

1106
01:43:58.566 --> 01:44:00.109
I need his help now.

1107
01:44:01.110 --> 01:44:02.319
Yes, sir.

1108
01:44:07.450 --> 01:44:08.659
Durant.

1109
01:44:09.368 --> 01:44:11.829
Michael Durant.

1110
01:44:12.580 --> 01:44:13.581
Yes.

1111
01:44:14.039 --> 01:44:16.459
You are the Ranger who kills my people?

1112
01:44:16.667 --> 01:44:20.045
I'm not a Ranger. I'm a pilot.

1113
01:44:24.008 --> 01:44:25.301
That's right.

1114
01:44:25.968 --> 01:44:28.971
None of you Americans smoke anymore.

1115
01:44:32.183 --> 01:44:36.812
You all live long, dull, uninteresting lives.

1116
01:44:38.689 --> 01:44:40.524
What do you want with me?

1117
01:44:41.358 --> 01:44:43.110
You have taken hostages.

1118
01:44:44.111 --> 01:44:45.696
We have you.

1119
01:44:45.905 --> 01:44:49.033
My government
will never negotiate for me.

1120
01:44:49.533 --> 01:44:54.121
Then perhaps you and I can negotiate, huh?

1121
01:44:55.581 --> 01:44:58.125
Soldier to soldier.

1122
01:45:04.048 --> 01:45:05.883
I'm not in charge.

1123
01:45:09.136 --> 01:45:13.557
Course not. You have the power to Kill,
but not negotiate.

1124
01:45:14.058 --> 01:45:16.936
In Somalia, killing is negotiation.

1125
01:45:18.521 --> 01:45:21.899
Do you really think
if you get General Aidid...

1126
01:45:22.066 --> 01:45:25.444
...we will simply put down our weapons...

1127
01:45:25.569 --> 01:45:28.572
...and adopt American democracy?

1128
01:45:29.031 --> 01:45:30.825
That the killing will stop?

1129
01:45:31.242 --> 01:45:35.287
We know this:
Without victory, there can be no peace.

1130
01:45:36.080 --> 01:45:38.499
There will always be killing, you see?

1131
01:45:38.958 --> 01:45:41.168
This is how things are in our world.

1132
01:45:54.014 --> 01:45:57.685
Mike Durant, we won't leave you behind.

1133
01:45:59.812 --> 01:46:03.274
Mike Durant, we won't leave you behind.

1134
01:46:05.985 --> 01:46:08.863
You got to take over from me. Both hands.

1135
01:46:16.579 --> 01:46:19.790
It's the femoral artery, but I can't see it.

1136
01:46:19.999 --> 01:46:23.460
Which means that
it's retracted up into the pelvis.

1137
01:46:23.669 --> 01:46:27.965
I have to find it and clamp it.
It's the only way to stop the bleeding.

1138
01:46:28.173 --> 01:46:30.301
I got no more IVs.

1139
01:46:31.552 --> 01:46:34.471
So, I'm going to need you to assist. Okay?

1140
01:46:34.597 --> 01:46:36.223
Yeah, yeah.

1141
01:46:37.141 --> 01:46:40.519
Now listen, Jamie.
I got to do something, it's going to hurt.

1142
01:46:41.812 --> 01:46:45.482
I got to cause you more pain,
but I have to do it to help you.

1143
01:46:45.691 --> 01:46:47.234
All right, you understand?

1144
01:46:47.318 --> 01:46:49.320
-Morphine.
- I can't.

1145
01:46:49.486 --> 01:46:52.114
It'll lower your heart rate too far.
I'm sorry.

1146
01:46:52.156 --> 01:46:54.491
Twombly, why don't you take his hands?

1147
01:46:58.996 --> 01:47:01.916
Hold the wound open,
keep pressure on the top of the leg.

1148
01:47:01.999 --> 01:47:04.168
Yurek, take the feet and a flashlight.

1149
01:47:04.585 --> 01:47:05.711
On my count.

1150
01:47:05.794 --> 01:47:07.796
All right, Jamie. All right.

1151
01:47:10.049 --> 01:47:12.217
One. Two.

1152
01:47:13.177 --> 01:47:14.219
Three.

1153
01:47:21.936 --> 01:47:24.355
Wait, wait. Okay. I feel it.

1154
01:47:25.022 --> 01:47:26.357
I feel the pulse.

1155
01:47:27.942 --> 01:47:29.276
I got it. I got it.

1156
01:47:29.360 --> 01:47:30.945
I got it, yeah. I got it.

1157
01:47:31.028 --> 01:47:32.613
- I got it.
-You got it?

1158
01:47:33.030 --> 01:47:34.031
Clamp?

1159
01:47:36.450 --> 01:47:37.826
I got it clamped.

1160
01:47:37.952 --> 01:47:39.161
-Hold it.
-Got it.

1161
01:47:39.203 --> 01:47:40.496
Here, grab it.

1162
01:47:41.163 --> 01:47:42.873
-It's tearing.
- I got it.

1163
01:47:43.123 --> 01:47:45.000
-Doc, it's going back in!
-Hold it!

1164
01:47:45.042 --> 01:47:46.293
