1166
01:47:50.839 --> 01:47:52.132
Move your hand.

1167
01:48:03.352 --> 01:48:04.561
What?

1168
01:48:23.706 --> 01:48:24.707
Fix it?

1169
01:48:28.293 --> 01:48:30.754
Yeah, yeah. We got it.

1170
01:48:46.395 --> 01:48:48.188
What the hell are you doing?

1171
01:48:48.272 --> 01:48:52.651
It's all in the grind, Sarg'nt.
Can't be too fine, can't be too coarse.

1172
01:48:52.860 --> 01:48:55.529
Grimesy, you are squared away.

1173
01:49:11.837 --> 01:49:15.799
Sarg'nt, how would you
like a nice hot cup of Joe?

1174
01:49:17.634 --> 01:49:19.219
Gold Coast blend.

1175
01:49:19.428 --> 01:49:22.347
Sit down.
I want to take a look at that foot.

1176
01:49:22.973 --> 01:49:25.059
-No, it's not a problem.
-Come on.

1177
01:49:31.482 --> 01:49:34.610
-Where the hell did they find you?
-Behind a desk.

1178
01:49:36.111 --> 01:49:39.156
No, really. What, you think I'm kidding?

1179
01:49:42.826 --> 01:49:44.620
-Is anybody hit?
-We're good!

1180
01:49:50.000 --> 01:49:51.168
You all right?

1181
01:49:51.210 --> 01:49:52.211
Yeah!

1182
01:49:52.419 --> 01:49:53.879
Is everybody all right?

1183
01:49:53.962 --> 01:49:55.005
Yeah!

1184
01:50:09.019 --> 01:50:10.187
Incoming!

1185
01:51:15.752 --> 01:51:17.754
DiTomasso's hit! Pull him out!

1186
01:51:51.246 --> 01:51:52.956
Ranger here. This is Kilo 11.

1187
01:51:53.040 --> 01:51:56.293
Chalk Four. We're at the southeast corner
of the crash. Who's this?

1188
01:51:56.335 --> 01:51:58.337
This is Hoot.
I'm coming with three friendlies.

1189
01:51:58.420 --> 01:52:00.088
I need cover fire. Over.

1190
01:52:00.130 --> 01:52:03.091
Roger, Kilo 11. Hold your fire!
Deltas coming in.

1191
01:52:03.133 --> 01:52:05.177
Hold your fire! Hold your fire!

1192
01:52:09.890 --> 01:52:14.519
Ground personnel will have to mark
target positions with infrared strobes.

1193
01:52:15.187 --> 01:52:18.982
Get little birds on strafing runs
and keep them going all night long.

1194
01:52:19.066 --> 01:52:21.318
If we don't hold back this city...

1195
01:52:22.027 --> 01:52:25.030
...we'll have a 100 caskets
to fill by morning.

1196
01:52:25.239 --> 01:52:26.490
Yes, sir.

1197
01:52:26.657 --> 01:52:29.451
Colonel Harrell,
ground personnel at crash site one...

1198
01:52:29.493 --> 01:52:33.997
...will have to mark the target
with infrared strobes to prep for air strike.

1199
01:52:39.294 --> 01:52:40.504
McKnight.

1200
01:52:44.591 --> 01:52:48.178
Between the 10th Mountain and U.N.,
we got enough personnel, okay?

1201
01:52:49.513 --> 01:52:52.349
Danny, you guys do not have to
go back out again.

1202
01:53:12.494 --> 01:53:15.038
I can't die here, man.

1203
01:53:16.206 --> 01:53:20.335
You're not going to die, all right?
You're not going to die.

1204
01:53:21.211 --> 01:53:22.713
I'm sorry.

1205
01:53:22.879 --> 01:53:26.174
You don't have anything to be sorry for.

1206
01:53:26.341 --> 01:53:29.511
You saved Twombly. You did perfect.

1207
01:53:30.721 --> 01:53:32.180
You okay, Twombs?

1208
01:53:32.723 --> 01:53:34.558
Yeah, I'm okay, Jamie.

1209
01:53:35.892 --> 01:53:38.103
You did what you were trained to do.

1210
01:53:39.062 --> 01:53:40.897
You should be proud of that.

1211
01:53:44.026 --> 01:53:45.360
Be proud of that.

1212
01:53:46.194 --> 01:53:48.071
-Ev?
-Yeah.

1213
01:53:50.032 --> 01:53:51.366
Do me a favor.

1214
01:53:54.411 --> 01:53:59.374
You tell my parents
that I fought well today.

1215
01:54:06.798 --> 01:54:08.675
And that I fought hard.

1216
01:54:10.635 --> 01:54:13.096
You're going to tell them yourself, okay?

1217
01:54:13.180 --> 01:54:14.514
Do you hear me?

1218
01:54:16.308 --> 01:54:17.392
All right?

1219
01:54:19.519 --> 01:54:22.647
-Are the humvees here?
-They're coming, Jamie.

1220
01:54:23.148 --> 01:54:24.983
They're coming.

1221
01:54:25.150 --> 01:54:27.444
You just got to hang in there a little bit.

1222
01:54:27.486 --> 01:54:29.988
-You hold on for just a little bit.
- can.

1223
01:54:30.155 --> 01:54:31.323
I can.

1224
01:54:32.699 --> 01:54:34.159
It's nothing.

1225
01:54:35.410 --> 01:54:36.828
It's nothing.

1226
01:54:37.871 --> 01:54:38.997
It's nothing.

1227
01:54:39.081 --> 01:54:41.416
-It's nothing.
-It's nothing.

1228
01:54:42.334 --> 01:54:43.502
Nothing.

1229
01:54:51.176 --> 01:54:52.177
Oh, shit.

1230
01:54:53.178 --> 01:54:54.513
Hold the wound.

1231
01:55:21.540 --> 01:55:22.833
Doc.

1232
01:55:25.710 --> 01:55:26.753
Doc.

1233
01:55:43.854 --> 01:55:45.188
It's okay.

1234
01:56:11.798 --> 01:56:13.258
What are you doing?

1235
01:56:16.636 --> 01:56:18.388
We need the ammo.

1236
01:56:26.646 --> 01:56:28.440
You did all you could here.

1237
01:56:28.982 --> 01:56:31.234
They should've sent a medivac.

1238
01:56:31.735 --> 01:56:35.405
Right now we'd be out there
defending another crashed chopper.

1239
01:56:35.655 --> 01:56:38.158
More men would get torn up.

1240
01:56:41.161 --> 01:56:42.496
Maybe.

1241
01:56:42.996 --> 01:56:45.874
See, you're thinking. Don't.

1242
01:56:45.957 --> 01:56:49.002
Because, Sergeant, you can't control
who gets hit or who doesn't.

1243
01:56:49.085 --> 01:56:51.838
Who falls out of a chopper or why.

1244
01:56:52.047 --> 01:56:54.674
It ain't up to you. It's just war.

1245
01:56:56.676 --> 01:56:58.678
Yeah, well, Smith's still dead.

1246
01:57:00.347 --> 01:57:04.935
-This all happened because Blackburn fell.
-Should have, could have, don't matter.

1247
01:57:05.101 --> 01:57:08.897
You'll get plenty of time
to think about all that later. Believe me.

1248
01:57:12.651 --> 01:57:15.779
Sergeant, you got your men this far.

1249
01:57:16.613 --> 01:57:18.323
You did it right today.

1250
01:57:18.532 --> 01:57:21.993
You need to start thinking about
getting these men out of here.

1251
01:57:28.416 --> 01:57:30.293
Well, shall we?

1252
01:57:39.052 --> 01:57:42.138
I need four guys in this corner now!

1253
01:57:48.311 --> 01:57:49.938
RPG!

1254
01:57:53.817 --> 01:57:56.319
This is Barber 52 in position for gun run.

1255
01:57:56.403 --> 01:57:58.530
Jesus Christ. Look at that.

1256
01:57:59.239 --> 01:58:02.284
This is 25! I can see you.
You're right above me.

1257
01:58:02.450 --> 01:58:05.870
Eversmann, I can't tell who's who
down there. Too much activity.

1258
01:58:05.954 --> 01:58:08.456
I'll mark the target with a strobe! Over.

1259
01:58:08.665 --> 01:58:09.833
Roger that.

1260
01:58:21.636 --> 01:58:22.804
You see it?

1261
01:58:25.140 --> 01:58:26.725
Nah, I can't see shit.

1262
01:58:27.684 --> 01:58:30.562
-I'm putting it on the roof.
-You're going to need help!

1263
01:58:30.645 --> 01:58:31.646
Cover me.

1264
01:58:32.856 --> 01:58:36.610
Okay, guys, we're going to lay down
some cover fire for him on three!

1265
01:58:36.818 --> 01:58:37.819
Ready?

1266
01:58:37.986 --> 01:58:38.987
One.

1267
01:58:39.029 --> 01:58:40.155
Two.

1268
01:58:40.322 --> 01:58:42.032
Three. Go!

1269
01:59:14.606 --> 01:59:18.068
I got your position. I got the target.
We're inbound and hot.

1270
01:59:42.634 --> 01:59:47.305
C-2, miniguns dry. Request permission
to return to base. Rearm. Over.

1271
01:59:47.472 --> 01:59:50.308
Roger that. Second team inbound.
Your station.

1272
01:59:50.475 --> 01:59:52.686
On your location, four minutes.

1273
02:00:00.819 --> 02:00:03.905
All right, they're here.
Get the wounded ready to move.

1274
02:00:04.364 --> 02:00:06.783
Lay down some cover fire!

1275
02:00:09.119 --> 02:00:11.246
I thought I heard a noise out here!

1276
02:00:11.287 --> 02:00:14.040
-Load up. We're getting out of here.
-Yes, sir.

1277
02:00:17.210 --> 02:00:21.965
25, this is 64. The rescue column's here
and will be with you in about 5 minutes.

1278
02:00:22.132 --> 02:00:23.883
Prepare your men for exfil.

1279
02:00:23.967 --> 02:00:26.469
Yeah, roger that, sir! Roger that!

1280
02:00:27.178 --> 02:00:30.974
Five minutes! The convoy is going to be
here in five minutes!

1281
02:00:50.910 --> 02:00:53.163
I need a mag! Eversmann, I'm out!

1282
02:00:53.329 --> 02:00:54.664
My last one!

1283
02:01:04.841 --> 02:01:07.010
The convoy is here!

1284
02:01:25.570 --> 02:01:29.115
Sergeant Eversmann.
I heard you guys needed a lift!

1285
02:01:29.365 --> 02:01:31.034
Yes, sir!

1286
02:01:31.201 --> 02:01:33.828
Bring your wounded
and start loading them up!

1287
02:01:41.044 --> 02:01:43.171
Hey, I got you. I got you.

1288
02:01:43.379 --> 02:01:46.090
It's okay. I want to walk.

1289
02:01:46.633 --> 02:01:49.719
Yeah, I would too. Let's go!

1290
02:01:58.895 --> 02:01:59.979
Move!

1291
02:02:03.233 --> 02:02:06.569
We get the pilots' bodies out,
and then we go to the stadium.

1292
02:02:07.237 --> 02:02:09.072
We're running out of room around here.

1293
02:02:09.113 --> 02:02:11.074
Cram into every possible space.

1294
02:02:11.908 --> 02:02:16.913
Okay, 10th Mountain provides security
for armor, walks us out of the hot zone.

1295
02:02:17.121 --> 02:02:18.623
10th Mountain? No.

1296
02:02:18.832 --> 02:02:21.918
Sir, with respect,
my Rangers can provide rear security.

1297
02:02:22.085 --> 02:02:26.256
We'll walk you out of the hot zone,
then we'll jump on the last few vehicles.

1298
02:02:27.257 --> 02:02:28.550
Okay, let's get out of here.

1299
02:02:28.591 --> 02:02:29.801
Let's go.

1300
02:02:30.009 --> 02:02:32.512
-All right, you got him?
-Yeah, come on.

1301
02:02:34.430 --> 02:02:35.807
Come on!

1302
02:02:36.933 --> 02:02:39.936
These things are fucking bullet magnets.
Come on, let's go!

1303
02:02:40.019 --> 02:02:42.438
We go when I'm ordered to, soldier.

1304
02:02:45.316 --> 02:02:46.526
Careful.

1305
02:02:47.110 --> 02:02:49.320
Easy. Go easy.

1306
02:02:52.740 --> 02:02:54.117
Easy.

1307
02:03:04.627 --> 02:03:06.838
Colonel, what is going on down there?

1308
02:03:06.921 --> 02:03:10.133
They're dismantling
the entire cockpit around the body.

1309
02:03:10.300 --> 02:03:13.970
How long is it going to take?
I need an honest, no-shit assessment.

1310
02:03:14.929 --> 02:03:16.306
They can't say!

1311
02:03:18.266 --> 02:03:19.475
Danny...

1312
02:03:20.977 --> 02:03:22.812
...no one gets left behind.

1313
02:03:23.479 --> 02:03:25.315
You understand me, son?

1314
02:03:25.815 --> 02:03:27.275
Yes, General.

1315
02:03:27.942 --> 02:03:29.569
Do what you have to do.

1316
02:03:30.945 --> 02:03:32.196
Roger.

1317
02:03:38.411 --> 02:03:41.080
-Come on. Bring him through.
- I got him.

1318
02:03:41.956 --> 02:03:45.126
-Get all his gear. Get the wounded out.
-Got you, sir!

1319
02:03:50.715 --> 02:03:52.133
-Move!
-Got you!

1320
02:03:52.800 --> 02:03:54.844
Move out! Move out! Let's go!

1321
02:04:04.896 --> 02:04:05.897
Fuck!

1322
02:04:08.733 --> 02:04:10.068
Fire in the hole!

1323
02:04:10.276 --> 02:04:12.111
-Let's go! Move!
-Let's go!

1324
02:04:22.664 --> 02:04:26.042
-Open the hatch! We got men back here!
-No room here! Go on the roof!

1325
02:04:26.125 --> 02:04:27.210
What's going on?

1326
02:04:27.293 --> 02:04:30.296
-The roof?
-I'm not getting on no fucking roof!

1327
02:04:31.255 --> 02:04:32.674
No, no, it's full.

1328
02:04:34.092 --> 02:04:37.387
We're running out. Keep moving.
Use the vehicles as cover.

1329
02:04:39.764 --> 02:04:41.849
Move it! Let's go!

1330
02:04:58.741 --> 02:05:01.285
All right, hold it up. Hold it up.

1331
02:05:03.287 --> 02:05:04.664
-Move!
-Go! Move!

1332
02:05:04.914 --> 02:05:06.249
Go!

1333
02:06:00.845 --> 02:06:03.306
Get down! Get down!

1334
02:06:04.515 --> 02:06:05.808
Get down, lady!

1335
02:06:08.311 --> 02:06:09.645
I'm out of ammo!

1336
02:06:11.022 --> 02:06:13.024
Sanderson, I'm out of ammo!

1337
02:06:18.029 --> 02:06:19.655
Don't you do it.

1338
02:06:20.239 --> 02:06:22.742
-What are you doing?
-Don't you damn do it.

1339
02:06:24.535 --> 02:06:25.912
Kurth, let's go!

1340
02:08:49.764 --> 02:08:51.265
Easy.

1341
02:09:41.148 --> 02:09:42.900
Ah, shit.

1342
02:09:42.984 --> 02:09:46.654
Bullet missed your jugular by
about three millimeters. Don't move.

1343
02:09:48.322 --> 02:09:50.366
Hurry up, hurry up.

1344
02:09:53.703 --> 02:09:57.707
Little short on coffee,
but I got you some tea.

1345
02:10:02.003 --> 02:10:03.629
How you doing, soldier?

1346
02:10:04.839 --> 02:10:06.716
Can't feel a thing.

1347
02:10:16.767 --> 02:10:18.394
Take his pulse.

1348
02:10:51.719 --> 02:10:53.095
Hey, Sarg'nt.

1349
02:10:57.683 --> 02:10:58.684
Captain.

1350
02:10:58.851 --> 02:11:01.854
Lorenzo. How you doing?

1351
02:11:04.440 --> 02:11:09.278
It went in and out, so the medic said
I should be okay in a couple of days.

1352
02:11:09.445 --> 02:11:11.155
That's great news.

1353
02:11:11.781 --> 02:11:13.449
Are we going after them?

1354
02:11:13.574 --> 02:11:16.285
You bet your ass we will.
We got to regroup.

1355
02:11:17.870 --> 02:11:19.789
Don't go out there without me.

1356
02:11:20.790 --> 02:11:24.293
Don't go back out there without me.

1357
02:11:25.044 --> 02:11:26.962
I can still do my job.

1358
02:11:28.714 --> 02:11:31.342
You get some rest now, okay?

1359
02:11:46.482 --> 02:11:47.900
You're going back in?

1360
02:11:49.985 --> 02:11:51.821
There are still men out there.

1361
02:11:54.240 --> 02:11:55.825
Goddamn.

1362
02:12:00.996 --> 02:12:02.289
When I go home...

1363
02:12:03.290 --> 02:12:04.792
...and people ask me:

1364
02:12:04.959 --> 02:12:08.295
"Hey, Hoot, why do you do it, man?

1365
02:12:08.838 --> 02:12:12.675
"Why? You some kind of war junkie?"

1366
02:12:13.509 --> 02:12:15.928
I won't say a goddamn word.

1367
02:12:16.262 --> 02:12:17.513
Why?

1368
02:12:18.139 --> 02:12:19.974
They won't understand.

1369
02:12:21.684 --> 02:12:24.019
They won't understand why we do it.

1370
02:12:25.521 --> 02:12:29.650
They won't understand
it's about the men next to you.

1371
02:12:31.485 --> 02:12:32.820
And that's it.

1372
02:12:34.989 --> 02:12:36.323
That's all it is.

1373
02:12:46.667 --> 02:12:51.046
Don't even think about it, all right?
I'm better on my own.

1374
02:12:56.177 --> 02:12:59.180
We started a whole new week.
It's Monday.

1375
02:13:12.026 --> 02:13:14.195
I was talking to Blackburn the other day...

1376
02:13:14.236 --> 02:13:18.949
...and he asked me, "What changed?
Why are we going home?”

1377
02:13:20.493 --> 02:13:22.828
And I said, "Nothing."

1378
02:13:23.037 --> 02:13:26.957
But that's not true, you know.
I think everything's changed.

1379
02:13:28.375 --> 02:13:29.877
I know I've changed.

1380
02:13:35.633 --> 02:13:38.344
A friend of mine asked me
before I got here....

1381
02:13:38.469 --> 02:13:40.763
It was when we were all shipping out.

1382
02:13:40.888 --> 02:13:42.389
He asked me:

1383
02:13:43.641 --> 02:13:46.393
"Why are you going to fight
somebody else's war?

1384
02:13:47.102 --> 02:13:49.522
"What, do y'all think you're heroes?"

1385
02:13:52.483 --> 02:13:54.902
I didn't know what to say at the time...

1386
02:13:57.821 --> 02:14:00.241
...but if he asked me again, I'd say no.

1387
02:14:02.785 --> 02:14:04.828
I'd say there's no way in hell.

1388
02:14:05.955 --> 02:14:07.957
Nobody asks to be a hero.

1389
02:14:13.295 --> 02:14:15.589
It just sometimes turns out that way.

1390
02:14:19.552 --> 02:14:22.638
I'll talk to your ma and pa
when I get home, okay?

1391
02:15:06.181 --> 02:15:09.893
My love, you are strong
and you will do well in life.

1392
02:15:10.936 --> 02:15:13.397
I love you and my children deeply.

1393
02:15:14.315 --> 02:15:17.818
Today and tomorrow,
let each day grow and grow.

1394
02:15:19.028 --> 02:15:23.198
Keep smiling and never give up,
even when things get you down.

1395
02:15:24.491 --> 02:15:26.910
So, in closing, my love...

1396
02:15:27.286 --> 02:15:31.123
...tonight, tuck my children in bed warmly.

1397
02:15:31.540 --> 02:15:36.170
Tell them I love them.
Then hug them for me...

1398
02:15:36.378 --> 02:15:39.256
...and give them both
a kiss good night for Daddy.

